column2: Pakistan International Airlines sacrifices goat, resumes ATR flights
column3: Images of Pakistan International Airlines sacrificing a goat went viral on Monday as the beleaguered state-run airline resumed ATR flights. All ten ATRs in its fleet were grounded in the aftermath of a crash near Havelian earlier in December.

column2: Australian Federal Court orders ISPs to block copyright infringing sites
column3: On Thursday, the Australian Federal Court ordered Internet service providers to block websites which infringe copyright.

column2: Despite defectors, U.S. electoral college affirms Trump presidency
column3: The U.S. electoral college voted on Monday to place Republican businessman Donald Trump in the presidency.

column2: Suárez signs contract extension with Barça
column3: On Friday, Catalonian football club FC Barcelona announced striker Luis Suarez signed a contract extension till June 2021.

column2: UEFA Champions League 2016-2017: Draw for Last 16 held at Nyon
column3: The draw for the Last 16 for the 2016–17 UEFA Champions League took place in Nyon, Switzerland at 12:00 local time.
